320 g Chicken Breast Tenders
6 unit(s) Flour Tortillas
56 g Red Cabbage, shredded
28 g Arugula and Spinach Mix
90 mL Dill Pickle, sliced
4 g Dill-Garlic Spice Blend
43 mL Creamy Dressing
28 g Crispy Shallots
1 tbsp Oil*
½ tsp Sugar*
0.13 tsp Salt*
0.13 tsp Pepper*

Before starting, preheat the broiler to high.
Wash and dry all produce.
Drain pickles. Reserve pickle juice.
To a medium bowl, add pickle juice, cabbage, half the creamy dressing, 1/2 tsp (1 tsp) sugar and 1/2 tbsp (1 tbsp) oil. Season with salt and pepper. Toss to coat.

Line a baking sheet with alumium foil.
Pat chicken dry with paper towels.
To the prepared baking sheet, add chicken, half the Dill-Garlic Spice Blend and 1/2 tbsp (1 tbsp) oil. Season with salt and pepper. Toss to coat, then arrange chicken in a single layer.
Broil chicken in the middle of the oven for 7-10 min, until golden and cooked through.**

While chicken cooks, roughly chop pickle.
To a small bowl, add pickles, remaining creamy dressing and remaining Dill-Garlic Spice Blend. Stir to combine.
Just before serving, wrap tortillas in paper towels. Microwave for 30 sec-1 min, until tortillas are warm and flexible. (TIP: You can skip this step if you don't want to warm the tortillas!)

Using two forks, gently flake chicken.
Arrange torillas on a clean surface.
Top with arugula-spinach mix, slaw, chicken, creamy pickle relish and crispy shallots.
Divide wraps between plates.